---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Fungi — Mushroom Terms That Score Big"
  description="Fungi and mushroom words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. TRUFFLE (13pts), MYCELIUM (17pts), SPORE (7pts). Mycology vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble fungi words, truffle scrabble points, mycelium scrabble, spore scrabble, mushroom words scrabble, mycology vocabulary scrabble, fungus words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Fungi — Mushroom Terms That Score Big","description":"Fungi and mushroom words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. TRUFFLE (13pts), MYCELIUM (17pts), SPORE (7pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-fungi"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is MYCELIUM a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! MYCELIUM scores 17 points (M=3, Y=4, C=3, E=1, L=1, I=1, U=1, M=3). The double M=3 plus Y=4 and C=3 make this 8-letter fungal network a powerful bingo candidate worth 67 total points."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is TRUFFLE worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"TRUFFLE scores 13 points (T=1, R=1, U=1, F=4, F=4, L=1, E=1). The double F=4 tiles carry this 7-letter word — a potential bingo play worth 63 total points."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you play SPORE in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. SPORE scores 7 points (S=1, P=3, O=1, R=1, E=1). A compact 5-letter word that hooks easily with S (SPORES, 8pts) and D (SPORED, 9pts) for flexible board placement."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Fungi — Mushroom Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">The fungal kingdom offers Scrabble players an underground network of high-scoring words. Double F tiles in TRUFFLE, the Y-M-C combination in MYCELIUM, and versatile hooks from SPORE make mycology a fertile ground for competitive play.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">17 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">MYCELIUM</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">13 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TRUFFLE</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">7 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SPORE</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">10 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">FUNGAL</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Fungi Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">MYCELIUM — 17 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">M=3, Y=4, C=3, E=1, L=1, I=1, U=1, M=3 · 8 letters · Bingo powerhouse</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The hidden root network of fungi delivers visible results on the Scrabble board. At 8 letters, MYCELIUM earns the 50-point bingo bonus — turning 17 base points into a massive 67-point play.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🍄 TRUFFLE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 pts · T=1, R=1, U=1, F=4, F=4, L=1, E=1 · Double F</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🧬 MYCELIUM</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">17 pts · M=3, Y=4, C=3, E=1, L=1, I=1, U=1, M=3 · Bingo</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌿 SPORE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">7 pts · S=1, P=3, O=1, R=1, E=1 · Hookable</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🍂 FUNGAL</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · F=4, U=1, N=1, G=2, A=1, L=1 · F+G combo</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Mycology Vocabulary</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">YEAST</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MOULD</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">LICHEN</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MOREL</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">HYPHA</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">16pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BLIGHT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Fungi Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">TRUFFLE doubles the F:</span> Two F=4 tiles deliver 8 of the word's 13 points. When you draw both F tiles, TRUFFLE is your highest-value natural play — and it's a bingo at 7 letters (63 total).</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">MYCELIUM is a premium bingo hunt:</span> M+Y+C alone give 10 points. With the 50-point bonus, MYCELIUM yields 67 points — worth holding tiles for if you have 5+ of the letters.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">SPORE is your flexible hook word:</span> Hooks with S (SPORES), D (SPORED), and even connects to parallel plays. Use it to bridge tight board positions when you need a reliable 7-pointer.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Fungi words excel at <span class="text-white font-medium">double-letter efficiency</span>. TRUFFLE (FF), MYCELIUM (MM), and common mushroom terms use doubled tiles that might otherwise clog your rack — turning a surplus into a scoring opportunity.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-nature-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Nature Words</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-garden/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from the Garden</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-biology/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Biology</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid fungi word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
